<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1618007-hi-all-great-story-but-one-consistent">Hi All,
GREAT story, but one consistent (annoying) grammatical error overlooked by author and obviously-every editor on the team;
 Each time Pears writes the word &quot;HISTORICAL&quot; preceded by an article, he uses &quot;AN.&quot;
&quot;An historical&quot;...event, etc. is wrong.
To confirm this, I checked out:.https://www.dailywritingtips.com/a-historic-vs-an-historic/.
Arguments?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1618007'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15888.An_Instance_of_the_Fingerpost">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1618007-hi-all-great-story-but-one-consistent">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1618007-hi-all-great-story-but-one-consistent">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
