<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">This was not an error.<br/><br/><a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='https://books.google.com/ngrams/graph?content=an+historical%2Ca+historical&amp;year_start=1650&amp;year_end=2019&amp;corpus=18&amp;smoothing=3&amp;share=&amp;direct_url=t1%3B%2Can%20historical%3B%2Cc0%3B.t1%3B%2Ca%20historical%3B%2Cc0'>https://books.google.com/ngrams/graph...</a><br/><br/>As you can see from the chart, &quot;an historical&quot; was the preferred way of writing up until<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">This was not an error.<br /><br /><a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://books.google.com/ngrams/graph?content=an+historical%2Ca+historical&amp;year_start=1650&amp;year_end=2019&amp;corpus=18&amp;smoothing=3&amp;share=&amp;direct_url=t1%3B%2Can%20historical%3B%2Cc0%3B.t1%3B%2Ca%20historical%3B%2Cc0">https://books.google.com/ngrams/graph...</a><br /><br />As you can see from the chart, "an historical" was the preferred way of writing up until the 1950s.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
